# paint.type AI Manifest (Level 1)

This is the AI manifest for the `container/` directory (Level 1) of paint.type.

## Purpose

This manifest describes the purpose and structure of the `container/` directory.

## Authority Split

- **Central protocol authority:** `standards/` repository
- **Local integration authority (this directory):** container/ specific configurations

## Canonical Files\n\n- `compose.toml` -- Configuration file\n- `.gatekeeper.yaml` -- YAML configuration\n- `ct-build.sh` -- Shell script\n- `manifest.toml` -- Configuration file\n- `entrypoint.sh` -- Shell script\n- `deploy.k9.ncl` -- deploy.k9 configuration or data\n- `compose.example.toml` -- Configuration file\n- `Containerfile` -- Container image definition\n- `vordr.toml` -- Configuration file\n\n## Invariants

1. All A2ML state files must live in `.machine_readable/` ONLY, never in the repo root.
2. Each directory at layer 1 must have its own `0.1-AI-MANIFEST.a2ml`.
3. Each directory must have a `README.adoc` describing purpose, contents, and function.
4. SPDX license identifiers must be consistent across all files (AGPL-3.0-or-later).

## Startup Checklist for Agents

1. Read this file (`0.1-AI-MANIFEST.a2ml`).
2. Read `README.adoc` for directory overview.
3. For subdirectories, navigate to their respective manifest files.
4. Never edit `.machine_readable/` files directly.
